Articles.Content:
I just installed 1.02 from Steam. It was a fresh install, as I had moved my 0.9 files elsewhere.

The game loaded suspiciously quickly - in a couple of seconds - and only mentioned the cockpit internals in the yellow text box on the loading screen, no parts showed.

Then in the options for my first save I noticed there were no flags to choose from, just a blank box. I entered the game and there were no parts in the VAB or SPH.

The parts are all successfully downloaded in Gamedata>Squad>Parts, with their .cfg files etc. The KSP>Parts folder is empty, but I think that has always been the case. I checked Steam for additional downloadable content but there is none. I tried the game a few more times but always with the same result - no parts. This is the case if I click Play in Steam, or if I load by clicking the KSP.x86_64 exec file

Any suggestions?

Edited May 7, 2015 by Oafman

Have you got all the asset files in /KSP_Data ?

There should be sharedassetsN.assets where N=0 to 17

Have you got all the asset files in /KSP_Data ?

There should be sharedassetsN.assets where N=0 to 17

Yes, they're all there

Does your log file have the texture load messages for any parts ?

i.e [LOG nn:nn:nn.nnn] Load(Texture): Squad/Parts/Aero/?????

The textures all load on my install before the models load, then configs are setup.

i.e [LOG nn:nn:nn.nnn] Load(Texture): Squad/Parts/Aero/?????

No, there are no texture load messages.

The log is showing errors for each part it has failed to load. For example:

[LOG 22:17:06.161] PartLoader: Compiling Part 'Squad/Parts/Electrical/z-200Battery/z-200Battery/batteryBankMini'

[ERR 22:17:06.161] PartCompiler: Cannot clone model from 'Squad/Parts/Electrical/z-200Battery' directory as model does not exist

There is a 'z-200Battery.cfg' file in that folder, as well as a 'ksp_m_batteryPack_diff.dds'. Should there be something else too?

Do you have a file in that folder called model.mu ?

It sounds like you have an incomplete download.

First try verifying the game cache in Steam, right click KSP, click Properties and Local Files, there's a button to verify the cache in there.

If that doesn't solve it then deleting the KSP/GameData folder then verifying should prompt Steam to replace all the missing files.

Deleting Gamedata fixed it.

Thank you both for your help.
